      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-absolute-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation — five operating conditions (MRL-5 primary result)",
      "description": "This is the primary credibility-bearing validation result for COU2. The CFD model's predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements obtained from a modified ASTM F1841 protocol conducted on a physical replica of the FDA generic centrifugal pump. Five operating conditions spanning the VAD envelope (flow rates 3–6 L/min; rotational speeds 2500–4000 RPM) were evaluated. For each condition, three independent in-vitro runs were performed; mean NIH and 95 % confidence intervals were computed from the experimental replicates. The CFD predictions, post-processed using the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model with a Monte Carlo ensemble of 2000 samples propagating inlet velocity profile uncertainty and fluid viscosity variability, yielded NIH values within the experimental confidence intervals for four of five conditions. The fifth condition (6 L/min, 4000 RPM) exhibited a 12 % over-prediction of NIH relative to the experimental mean, which remains within the pre-specified 15 % acceptance band. The validation team (Morrison Lab, University of Alberta, 2024) conducted all experimental runs between 2024-03-11 and 2024-04-02 using the same fluid lot (bovine blood, anticoagulated with EDTA, hematocrit 33 ± 1 %). Pump hardware was inspected for dimensional conformance before each run. All raw experimental data are archived in the Morrison Lab LIMS under accession ML-2024-VAD-HLY-001 through ML-2024-VAD-HLY-015. Despite this detailed narrative, the structured provenance link to the generating computational and experimental activity has not been recorded in machine-readable form.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-in-vitro-mrl5"
